=C2=A0this document is not for investors. There is not much here that will =
be of much interest to people who are seriously considering buying DWAC sto=
ck, or who own DWAC stock and are considering whether to approve the TMTG m=
erger. (They obviously will, by the way: If the merger falls through, DWAC =
shareholders get back about $10 per share; the stock is trading at about $4=
