t this and get back to you,=E2=80=9D and they thought about it, and their c=
onclusion was that Goldman=E2=80=99s senior=C2=A0partners=C2=A0need unlimit=
ed vacations:Goldman Sachs has told its most senior bankers they will be al=
lowed to take as much holiday as they want so they can =E2=80=9Crest and re=
charge=E2=80=9D.=C2=A0Under a new =E2=80=9Cflexible vacation=E2=80=9D schem=
e introduced from May 1, partners and managing directors will be free to =
=E2=80=9Ctake time off when needed without a fixed vacation day entitlement=
=E2=80=9D, the Wall Street bank told staff in a memo last month.More junior=
 bankers, who will still be entitled to take only a fixed number of paid da=
ys off, have been given a minimum of two extra days of holiday per year. =
=E2=80=A6The changes follow scrutiny of Goldman=E2=80=99s working practices=
